Package Main

Class Pharmacist

Object
Pharmacist
public class Pharmacist extends Object
Represents a Pharmacist in the medical management system. Provides functionality for viewing and updating prescriptions, managing medication inventory, and handling appointment outcome records. Utilizes various managers for appointment, inventory, and prescription handling.
Since:
2024-11-6
Version:
1.0
Author:

  • Constructor Details

    • Pharmacist

      public Pharmacist(String userID, String userRole, Logger logger, dataReader reader, dataWriter writer)
      Constructs a Pharmacist object with the specified user information and data managers.
      Parameters:
      userID - the unique identifier for the pharmacist.
      userRole - the role of the user (expected to be "Pharmacist").
      logger - the logging utility for recording actions.
      reader - the data reader for retrieving information.
      writer - the data writer for saving information.

  • Method Details

    • menu

      public void menu()
      Displays the main menu for the pharmacist to perform various tasks. Logs the pharmacist's actions and processes menu choices in a loop.

    • viewAppointmentOutcomeRecord

      private void viewAppointmentOutcomeRecord()
      Views a specific appointment outcome record. Allows the pharmacist to choose between viewing a specific record or all records.

    • updatePrescriptionStatus

      private void updatePrescriptionStatus()
      Updates the prescription status or dispenses items based on appointment outcome records.

    • dispenseItemByAppointmentID

      private void dispenseItemByAppointmentID()
      Dispenses an item based on an appointment outcome ID. Prompts the pharmacist for the appointment outcome ID and dispenses the corresponding items.

    • dispenseItemByMedicineName

      private void dispenseItemByMedicineName()
      Dispenses a specified quantity of a medicine by its name. Prompts the pharmacist for the medicine name and quantity to dispense.

    • viewMedicationInventory

      private void viewMedicationInventory()
      Views the current medication inventory. Logs the action and retrieves the inventory from the inventory management system.

    • submitReplenishmentRequest

      private void submitReplenishmentRequest()
      Submits a request to replenish medication inventory. Prompts the pharmacist for the item name and quantity to request.
